==Wives==
I read in László Markó's work (2006 edition, I know it's not exactly the best source for that), Stephen II married the daughter of [[Robert I of Capua]], however her first name is unknown. So, the name [[Cristiana of Capua|Cristiana]] might be a fiction (unreferenced article). And what about Stephen's alleged second wife? Is [[Adelaide of Riedenburg|she]] really a [[hoax]]? --[[User:Norden1990|Norden1990]] ([[User talk:Norden1990|talk]]) 11:45, 6 January 2014 (UTC)
:::I agree that her name is only an invention. I am sure that the second wife is only a hoax (Hungarian chronicles emphasize that Stephen did not want to marry), but this is my own view. [[User:Borsoka|Borsoka]] ([[User talk:Borsoka|talk]]) 14:15, 6 January 2014 (UTC)
::::Hi.  I reverted the edit by [[User:Borsoka|Borsoka]] regarding the wife being named Cristiana, solely on the basis that the edit included the link to Cristiana's wikipage.  Either we know the name was Cristiana, in which case the current verbiage should stand, or we don't, in which case her name (and the link to the wikipage) should both be removed.  [[User:Onel5969|Onel5969]] ([[User talk:Onel5969|talk]]) 12:31, 5 May 2014 (UTC)
::::I opted for deleting the wikilink, since the article [[Cristiana of Capua]] is obviously OR. Her name is unknown. [[User:Borsoka|Borsoka]] ([[User talk:Borsoka|talk]]) 14:02, 5 May 2014 (UTC)

